item.title: COVID Research
item.description: #About The data in this research project is downloaded from the CDC Covid-19 Case Surveillance Data. # URL link to CDC to download data url <- "https://data.cdc.gov/api/views/vbim-akqf/rows.csv?accessType=DOWNLOAD" covid_data <- vroom::vroom(url)%>% clean_names() ##Task Given the data we have, I set out to create two graphs showing the deaathrate in combination with age group, sex, and whether the patient had co-morbidities or not age group, sex, and whether the patient was admited to Intensive Care Unit (ICU) or not.

item.title: IMDB Ratings: Does the director play a role?
item.description: #About This project was done to research whether the IMDB rating for blockbuster movies were influenced by the director. Before looking at any kind of data, a null hypothesis and alternative hypothesis were set up as follows: ###Null Hypothesis * H0 there is no difference in the mean IMDB-rating for movies produced by Steven Spielberg or Tim Burton. ###Alternative Hypothesis * Ha There is a significant difference between these mean IMDB-ratings.
